---
import Layout from "../../layouts/Layout.astro";
import Navbar from "../../components/Navbar.astro";
import Footer from "../../components/Footer.astro";

// Schema Markup for SEO
const articleSchema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "BlogPosting",
  "headline": "Best AI Image Generators in 2026: Unbiased Editorial Review",
  "description": "Compare the best AI image generators in 2026. Non-sponsored, deep editorial reviews, pricing, pros, cons, and guide for Midjourney, ChatGPT, Flux, Ideogram, Recraft, and Adobe Firefly.",
  "datePublished": "2026-06-11T08:30:00Z",
  "dateModified": "2026-06-11T08:30:00Z",
  "author": {
    "@type": "Organization",
    "name": "Imperial Picks Editorial Team",
    "url": "https://imperialpicks.in/about"
  },
  "publisher": {
    "@type": "Organization",
    "name": "Imperial Picks",
    "logo": {
      "@type": "ImageObject",
      "url": "https://imperialpicks.in/favicon.svg"
    }
  },
  "mainEntityOfPage": {
    "@type": "WebPage",
    "@id": "https://imperialpicks.in/ai-tools/best-ai-image-generators"
  }
};

const faqSchema = {
  "@context": "https://schema.org",
  "@type": "FAQPage",
  "mainEntity": [
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Which AI image generator is best for rendering clear text and typography?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Ideogram (v2.0 / v3.0) and Flux (Flux.1 Pro/Dev) are the industry leaders for rendering clear text and typography. Ideogram in particular is specifically designed to handle long sentences, labels, and graphic designs inside generated images without spelling errors, while Flux also displays high precision when prompted with shorter text strings."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Is there a completely free AI image generator that is commercially safe?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Adobe Firefly offers a free tier with monthly generative credits and is designed to be commercially safe. Firefly is trained exclusively on licensed content, such as Adobe Stock, and public domain images. While other open-source models like Flux.1 Schnell are free to run locally, they require technical setup and have different commercial licensing restrictions depending on the specific model variation."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Can I run Flux.1 locally on my computer?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Yes, Flux.1 Dev and Flux.1 Schnell can be run locally using tools like ComfyUI, Forge, or Diffusionbee. However, they require a modern system with a dedicated graphics card. For Flux.1 Dev, a GPU with at least 12GB to 16GB of VRAM is recommended, while Flux.1 Schnell can run on lower-spec hardware (8GB VRAM) using quantization (FP8 or FP4)."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Does ChatGPT's image generation support custom aspect ratios?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Yes. When using ChatGPT's DALL-E integration, you can request specific aspect ratios (such as square 1:1, widescreen 16:9, or vertical 9:16) directly in your conversational prompts. ChatGPT will adjust the output layout accordingly."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What is Recraft V3's primary advantage over Midjourney?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Recraft V3's primary advantage is its ability to generate true vector graphics (SVG files) and manage detailed brand design consistency. While Midjourney is excellent for cinematic and photorealistic raster graphics (PNG/JPG), Recraft can export clean vector shapes, icons, and illustrations that designers can edit in software like Illustrator or Figma."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Are AI-generated images copyrighted?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "In many jurisdictions, including the United States, pure AI-generated outputs without human modification cannot be copyrighted, as copyright requires human authorship. However, if a designer significantly edits, combines, or uses the AI outputs as part of a larger creative project, that final combined work may qualify for copyright protection."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How does Midjourney's web interface compare to its Discord server?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Midjourney's web interface is cleaner and more user-friendly, offering visual sliders for parameters like aspect ratio, stylization, chaos, and model versions. While the Discord interface remains active for community chats and legacy users, the web portal is now the recommended workspace for editing, organizational folders, and visual prompt mixing."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Can I generate commercial work using Midjourney?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Yes, Midjourney allows commercial use of generated images for all paid subscription plans. However, if you are an employee of a company with gross revenues exceeding $1,000,000 per year, you must subscribe to the Pro or Mega plans to use the images for commercial assets."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "How does Adobe Firefly protect against copyright issues?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Adobe trains Firefly models exclusively on datasets that it has the rights to use, including Adobe Stock datasets, licensed material, and public domain images. Adobe also provides IP indemnification for enterprise clients, meaning they will defend and cover damages if a client is sued for copyright infringement over a Firefly-generated image."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "What is Flux's 'Flow Matching' architecture?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Flow Matching is an alternative method to standard diffusion models for training generative networks. It learns direct paths between noise and clean images, which enables faster sampling, better training stability, and higher text alignment. This architecture allows Flux models to render complex prompt details and accurate typography in fewer steps."
      }
    },
    {
      "@type": "Question",
      "name": "Which AI image generator is best for creating marketing mockups?",
      "acceptedAnswer": {
        "@type": "Answer",
        "text": "Ideogram is excellent for product mockups with text labels, Recraft is ideal for clean graphic assets and vector designs, and Midjourney excels at high-end lifestyle and product photography mockups. The best option depends on whether your design requires precise text, editable vectors, or photorealistic lighting."
      }
    }
  ]
};
import Breadcrumbs from "../../components/Breadcrumbs.astro";
import AuthorBox from "../../components/AuthorBox.astro";
import RelatedArticles from "../../components/RelatedArticles.astro";
---

<Layout title="Best AI Image Generators in 2026: Unbiased Editorial Review - Imperial Picks" description="Compare the top AI image generators in 2026. Non-sponsored, deep reviews, pricing, pros, cons, and guide for Midjourney, ChatGPT, Flux, Ideogram, Recraft, and Adobe Firefly.">
  
  <!-- Inject JSON-LD Schema -->
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(articleSchema)} />
  <script type="application/ld+json" set:html={JSON.stringify(faqSchema)} />

  <Navbar />
  
  <main class="relative bg-slate-50 min-h-screen py-12">
    <!-- Background Patterns -->
    <div class="absolute inset-0 bg-grid-pattern pointer-events-none"></div>

    <div class="mx-auto max-w-7xl px-4 sm:px-6 lg:px-8">
      
      <!-- Breadcrumbs -->
      <Breadcrumbs items={[
        { label: "Home", link: "/" },
        { label: "AI Tools", link: "/ai-tools" },
        { label: "Best AI Image Generators" }
      ]} />

      <!-- Layout Grid: Left Content (Prose), Right Sticky Table of Contents -->
      <div class="grid grid-cols-1 lg:grid-cols-12 gap-12 relative z-10">
        
        <!-- Main Article Body (Prose) -->
        <article class="lg:col-span-8 bg-white border border-slate-200/80 rounded-3xl p-6 sm:p-10 lg:p-12 shadow-xs max-w-none">
          
          <!-- Article Header -->
          <header class="border-b border-slate-100 pb-8 mb-8">
            <span class="inline-flex items-center rounded-md bg-indigo-50 px-2.5 py-1 text-xs font-bold text-indigo-700 mb-4">
              Creative Stack
            </span>
            <h1 class="font-display text-3xl sm:text-4xl md:text-5xl font-black text-slate-900 tracking-tight leading-[1.15] mb-6">
              Best AI Image Generators in 2026: Unbiased Editorial Review
            </h1>
            
            <!-- Author Card -->
            <div class="flex items-center gap-3">
              <div class="h-10 w-10 rounded-full bg-indigo-600 text-indigo-50 flex items-center justify-center font-display text-sm font-bold shadow-sm">
                IP
              </div>
              <div class="text-xs">
                <p class="font-bold text-slate-800">Imperial Picks Editorial Team</p>
                <p class="text-slate-400 font-medium mt-0.5">Published on June 11, 2026 • 22 min read</p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </header>

          <!-- Introduction Section -->
          <section id="introduction" class="prose max-w-[72ch]">
            <h2 class="sr-only">Introduction</h2>
            <p class="text-base sm:text-lg text-slate-600 leading-relaxed font-medium mb-6">
              The field of AI-generated imagery has evolved from a hobbyist novelty into an essential component of modern creative workflows. In the early days of diffusion models, users struggled with deformed anatomy, mangled fingers, and abstract, nonsensical text rendering. Generating a usable asset was a matter of trial and error, requiring complex prompt engineering and significant post-processing.
            </p>
            <p class="text-sm sm:text-base text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
              In 2026, the technology has matured. The leading image generators are now highly specialized, production-ready design tools. Modern models leverage Flow Matching architectures, advanced text encoders (such as T5-XXL), and visual transformer pipelines to produce photorealistic results, render clean typography, and export scaleable vector layers.
            </p>
            <p class="text-sm sm:text-base text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
              However, this specialization means that a single tool can no longer handle every design requirement. A marketing agency creating lifestyle mockups needs a different feature set than a product designer generating vector UI elements, or a publisher requiring precise typographical layouts. Furthermore, considerations around commercial safety, database training sources, and data portability have become critical factors in tool selection.
            </p>
            <p class="text-sm sm:text-base text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
              To help you choose the right tools for your creative workflows, the Imperial Picks Editorial Team has conducted an independent audit of the leading image generation platforms. We evaluate the core strengths, weaknesses, licensing policies, and pricing structures of the six best AI image generators in 2026.
            </p>

            <!-- Callout: Trust & Data Integrity -->
            <div class="border-l-4 border-indigo-500 bg-indigo-50/50 p-5 rounded-r-2xl mb-8">
              <div class="flex gap-2">
                <span class="text-lg">⚖️</span>
                <div>
                  <h4 class="font-bold text-indigo-900 text-sm">Unbiased Editorial Standard</h4>
                  <p class="text-xs text-indigo-800 leading-relaxed mt-1">
                    This review is completely independent and non-sponsored. We do not use affiliate links, receive marketing kickbacks, or accept sponsorships from AI providers. Our reviews are based strictly on hands-on testing, prompt adherence, quality metrics, and cost-to-value evaluations.
                  </p>
                </div>
              </div>
            </div>
          </section>

          <!-- Quick Comparison Table -->
          <section id="comparison-table" class="mt-12 scroll-mt-20">
            <h2 class="font-display text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 tracking-tight mb-6 pb-2 border-b border-slate-100">
              Quick Comparison: AI Image Generators
            </h2>
            <p class="text-sm text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
              The table below summarizes the key trade-offs in features, pricing structures, and core strengths among the top image generators in 2026.
            </p>
            
            <div class="overflow-x-auto rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-slate-50/50 p-1 mb-8">
              <table class="w-full text-left text-sm border-collapse bg-white rounded-xl overflow-hidden">
                <thead>
                  <tr class="bg-slate-900 text-white font-display text-xs uppercase tracking-wider">
                    <th class="py-4 px-4 font-semibold">Generator</th>
                    <th class="py-4 px-4 font-semibold">Best For</th>
                    <th class="py-4 px-4 font-semibold">Free Plan</th>
                    <th class="py-4 px-4 font-semibold">Starting Price</th>
                    <th class="py-4 px-4 font-semibold">Core Strengths</th>
                  </tr>
                </thead>
                <tbody class="divide-y divide-slate-100 text-slate-700">
                  <tr class="hover:bg-slate-50/80 transition-colors">
                    <td class="py-4 px-4 font-bold text-slate-900">Midjourney</td>
                    <td class="py-4 px-4">Cinematic photorealism & artistic compositions</td>
                    <td class="py-4 px-4">
                      <span class="inline-flex items-center rounded-md bg-rose-50 px-2 py-1 text-xs font-semibold text-rose-800 border border-rose-200/50">No (Paid only)</span>
                    </td>
                    <td class="py-4 px-4 font-semibold text-slate-900">$10/month</td>
                    <td class="py-4 px-4 text-xs">Rich lighting, artistic styles, advanced web editor</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr class="hover:bg-slate-50/80 transition-colors">
                    <td class="py-4 px-4 font-bold text-slate-900">ChatGPT Image</td>
                    <td class="py-4 px-4">Conversational prompting & quick edits</td>
                    <td class="py-4 px-4">
                      <span class="inline-flex items-center rounded-md bg-emerald-50 px-2 py-1 text-xs font-semibold text-emerald-800 border border-emerald-200/50">Yes (Limited GPT-4o)</span>
                    </td>
                    <td class="py-4 px-4 font-semibold text-slate-900">$20/month (Plus)</td>
                    <td class="py-4 px-4 text-xs">Strong prompt alignment, in-chat editing, simple interface</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr class="hover:bg-slate-50/80 transition-colors">
                    <td class="py-4 px-4 font-bold text-slate-900">Flux (Black Forest)</td>
                    <td class="py-4 px-4">Open-source flexibility & text accuracy</td>
                    <td class="py-4 px-4">
                      <span class="inline-flex items-center rounded-md bg-emerald-50 px-2 py-1 text-xs font-semibold text-emerald-800 border border-emerald-200/50">Yes (Local/Schnell)</span>
                    </td>
                    <td class="py-4 px-4 font-semibold text-slate-900">Free (or API pay-as-you-go)</td>
                    <td class="py-4 px-4 text-xs">Local deployment, high prompt adherence, clear text</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr class="hover:bg-slate-50/80 transition-colors">
                    <td class="py-4 px-4 font-bold text-slate-900">Ideogram</td>
                    <td class="py-4 px-4">Typography & graphic design layouts</td>
                    <td class="py-4 px-4">
                      <span class="inline-flex items-center rounded-md bg-emerald-50 px-2 py-1 text-xs font-semibold text-emerald-800 border border-emerald-200/50">Yes (10 credits/day)</span>
                    </td>
                    <td class="py-4 px-4 font-semibold text-slate-900">$8/month</td>
                    <td class="py-4 px-4 text-xs">Excellent text rendering, graphic templates, prompt parsing</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr class="hover:bg-slate-50/80 transition-colors">
                    <td class="py-4 px-4 font-bold text-slate-900">Recraft</td>
                    <td class="py-4 px-4">Vector assets, SVGs & brand kits</td>
                    <td class="py-4 px-4">
                      <span class="inline-flex items-center rounded-md bg-emerald-50 px-2 py-1 text-xs font-semibold text-emerald-800 border border-emerald-200/50">Yes (Basic raster/public)</span>
                    </td>
                    <td class="py-4 px-4 font-semibold text-slate-900">$12/month</td>
                    <td class="py-4 px-4 text-xs">True SVG export, brand style management, visual consistency</td>
                  </tr>
                  <tr class="hover:bg-slate-50/80 transition-colors">
                    <td class="py-4 px-4 font-bold text-slate-900">Adobe Firefly</td>
                    <td class="py-4 px-4">Commercial safety & Creative Cloud workflows</td>
                    <td class="py-4 px-4">
                      <span class="inline-flex items-center rounded-md bg-emerald-50 px-2 py-1 text-xs font-semibold text-emerald-800 border border-emerald-200/50">Yes (25 credits/month)</span>
                    </td>
                    <td class="py-4 px-4 font-semibold text-slate-900">$4.99/month</td>
                    <td class="py-4 px-4 text-xs">Licensed training data, Photoshop/Illustrator sync, IP indemnity</td>
                  </tr>
                </tbody>
              </table>
            </div>
          </section>

          <!-- Detailed Reviews Section -->
          <section id="detailed-reviews" class="mt-16 space-y-20">
            <h2 class="font-display text-2xl sm:text-3xl font-bold text-slate-900 tracking-tight pb-2 border-b border-slate-100">
              Detailed Reviews: The Top 6 AI Image Generators
            </h2>

            <!-- Review: Midjourney -->
            <div id="tool-midjourney" class="scroll-mt-20">
              <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
                <span class="flex h-10 w-10 items-center justify-center rounded-xl bg-purple-50 text-purple-600 border border-purple-100 font-bold font-display">01</span>
                <h3 class="font-display text-2xl font-extrabold text-slate-900">Midjourney: The Artistic Standard</h3>
              </div>
              
              <p class="text-sm sm:text-base text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
                Midjourney continues to lead the industry for pure aesthetic appeal, cinematic lighting, and photorealistic detail. While early versions required using Discord, Midjourney's web interface now offers a complete standalone portal.
              </p>
              <p class="text-sm sm:text-base text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
                Midjourney excels at complex artistic composition and stylized lighting. It has a deep understanding of photographic styles, camera lenses, historical art periods, and atmospheric effects. However, it requires a learning curve for parameter controls (stylization, chaos, raw modes) to achieve specific layout alignments.
              </p>

              <h4 class="font-display text-sm font-bold text-slate-800 mb-3">Key Features</h4>
              <ul class="list-disc pl-5 mb-6 text-sm text-slate-600 space-y-2">
                <li><strong>Advanced Web Editor:</strong> Adjust aspect ratios, stylization levels, chaos values, and model versions via clean sliders, and use inpainting to edit specific details.</li>
                <li><strong>Vary Region (Inpainting):</strong> Select specific parts of an image to rewrite, add, or remove elements using text prompts.</li>
                <li><strong>Style & Character Reference:</strong> Use `--sref` and `--cref` parameters to maintain visual style and character consistency across multiple generations.</li>
              </ul>

              <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-6">
                <!-- Pros -->
                <div class="p-5 rounded-2xl bg-emerald-50/30 border border-emerald-100">
                  <h4 class="font-display font-bold text-emerald-950 text-sm mb-3">✓ Advantages</h4>
                  <ul class="list-disc pl-4 space-y-2 text-xs text-emerald-800">
                    <li>Unmatched rendering of lighting, skin textures, and artistic styles.</li>
                    <li>Highly active community and shared web gallery for inspiration.</li>
                    <li>Consistent character and style parameters enable sequential storytelling.</li>
                  </ul>
                </div>
                <!-- Cons -->
                <div class="p-5 rounded-2xl bg-rose-50/30 border border-rose-100">
                  <h4 class="font-display font-bold text-rose-950 text-sm mb-3">✗ Disadvantages</h4>
                  <ul class="list-disc pl-4 space-y-2 text-xs text-rose-800">
                    <li>No free plan available; requires a monthly subscription.</li>
                    <li>Can occasionally favor aesthetics over exact prompt adherence.</li>
                    <li>No native vector support; raster files only.</li>
                  </ul>
                </div>
              </div>

              <!-- Callout: Midjourney Details -->
              <div class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-slate-50/50 p-5 space-y-3 text-sm">
                <p><strong>Pricing:</strong> Basic Plan starts at $10/month (provides 3.3 hours of fast GPU time). Standard Plan is $30/month (adds unlimited relaxed generations).</p>
                <p><strong>Best Use Cases:</strong> Creative illustrations, cinematic photography, concept art, editorial layouts, and style-consistent character designs.</p>
                <p><strong>Verdict:</strong> The premier choice for artists, art directors, and designers who prioritize cinematic styling and detailed visual rendering.</p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Review: ChatGPT Image Generation -->
            <div id="tool-chatgpt" class="scroll-mt-20 border-t border-slate-100 pt-12">
              <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
                <span class="flex h-10 w-10 items-center justify-center rounded-xl bg-indigo-50 text-indigo-600 border border-indigo-100 font-bold font-display">02</span>
                <h3 class="font-display text-2xl font-extrabold text-slate-900">ChatGPT Image Generation: The Conversational Partner</h3>
              </div>
              
              <p class="text-sm sm:text-base text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
                OpenAI's image generation (built on DALL-E) is directly integrated into the ChatGPT chat window. It offers a highly conversational creation process, translating simple user prompts into detailed prompt descriptions behind the scenes to maximize model alignment.
              </p>
              <p class="text-sm sm:text-base text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
                Rather than writing complex parameter codes, you can chat with the assistant to refine your images. If an image is too dark, you can simply reply, "Make the lighting warmer and add a coffee cup to the table," and the model will adjust the composition. The built-in canvas editor also allows you to select specific areas of an image and describe edits conversational.
              </p>

              <h4 class="font-display text-sm font-bold text-slate-800 mb-3">Key Features</h4>
              <ul class="list-disc pl-5 mb-6 text-sm text-slate-600 space-y-2">
                <li><strong>Conversational Prompt Expansion:</strong> ChatGPT automatically expands short prompts, adding detail and stylistic context to ensure coherent outputs.</li>
                <li><strong>Visual Canvas Editor:</strong> Highlight specific areas of a generated image and describe edits to add, remove, or modify elements.</li>
                <li><strong>Flexible Aspect Ratios:</strong> Supports square, landscape, and vertical aspect ratios directly through natural language requests.</li>
              </ul>

              <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-6">
                <!-- Pros -->
                <div class="p-5 rounded-2xl bg-emerald-50/30 border border-emerald-100">
                  <h4 class="font-display font-bold text-emerald-950 text-sm mb-3">✓ Advantages</h4>
                  <ul class="list-disc pl-4 space-y-2 text-xs text-emerald-800">
                    <li>Very easy to use, with no prompt formatting codes required.</li>
                    <li>Strong prompt alignment makes it simple to generate complex descriptions.</li>
                    <li>Good basic text rendering within shapes and signs.</li>
                  </ul>
                </div>
                <!-- Cons -->
                <div class="p-5 rounded-2xl bg-rose-50/30 border border-rose-100">
                  <h4 class="font-display font-bold text-rose-950 text-sm mb-3">✗ Disadvantages</h4>
                  <ul class="list-disc pl-4 space-y-2 text-xs text-rose-800">
                    <li>Outputs can occasionally look overly clean, digital, or synthetic.</li>
                    <li>Limited manual control over specific rendering settings like seed or styles.</li>
                    <li>High usage limits are locked behind the $20/month Plus subscription.</li>
                  </ul>
                </div>
              </div>

              <!-- Callout: ChatGPT Image Details -->
              <div class="rounded-2xl border border-slate-200 bg-slate-50/50 p-5 space-y-3 text-sm">
                <p><strong>Pricing:</strong> Free basic access (limited daily credits). ChatGPT Plus costs $20/month (unlocks high priority generation, custom GPTs, and advanced reasoning models).</p>
                <p><strong>Best Use Cases:</strong> Quick sketches, ideation, educational illustrations, simple graphic assets, and social media posts.</p>
                <p><strong>Verdict:</strong> Best for beginners and professionals who want a simple, conversational interface without managing complex generation parameters.</p>
              </div>
            </div>

            <!-- Review: Flux -->
            <div id="tool-flux" class="scroll-mt-20 border-t border-slate-100 pt-12">
              <div class="flex items-center gap-3 mb-4">
                <span class="flex h-10 w-10 items-center justify-center rounded-xl bg-orange-50 text-orange-600 border border-orange-100 font-bold font-display">03</span>
                <h3 class="font-display text-2xl font-extrabold text-slate-900">Flux: The Open-Source Powerhouse</h3>
              </div>
              
              <p class="text-sm sm:text-base text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
                Flux, developed by Black Forest Labs (created by members of the original Stable Diffusion team), has established itself as the leading open-source model family. Flux utilizes a Diffusion Transformer (DiT) architecture combined with Flow Matching to achieve high prompt adherence and detail rendering.
              </p>
              <p class="text-sm sm:text-base text-slate-600 leading-relaxed mb-6">
                Flux is available in three distinct model sizes: *Flux.1 Schnell* (fast, open-source, local-friendly), *Flux.1 Dev* (high-quality, open-weights, non-commercial), and *Flux.1 Pro* (closed-source, API-accessible, commercial quality). Because the weights are open, developers can run Flux locally, train custom checkpoints, and integrate it into custom workflows.
              </p>

              <h4 class="font-display text-sm font-bold text-slate-800 mb-3">Key Features</h4>
              <ul class="list-disc pl-5 mb-6 text-sm text-slate-600 space-y-2">
                <li><strong>Open-Source Customization:</strong> Run models locally on consumer hardware, train custom LoRA models, and build custom ComfyUI workflows.</li>
                <li><strong>Excellent Typography:</strong> High precision when rendering text, labels, signs, and lettering directly within generated scenes.</li>
                <li><strong>High Prompt Adherence:</strong> Accurately parses long, complex, and highly detailed descriptions with fewer errors in object relationships.</li>
              </ul>

              <div class="grid grid-cols-1 sm:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-6">
